    <releaseNotes>https://antigravity.google/changelog</releaseNotes>
    <summary>Antigravity CLI - the terminal/TUI build of Google Antigravity (installed command: agy).</summary>
    <description>
**This is an unofficial, community-maintained package.** It is not maintained by or affiliated with Google.

The [Antigravity CLI](https://antigravity.google/) is the lightweight terminal (TUI) surface of Google Antigravity, bringing its agentic capabilities - multi-step reasoning, multi-file editing, tool calling, and conversation history - directly to your terminal. It is the terminal successor to the Gemini CLI.

This package downloads the official Antigravity CLI portable binary at install time directly from Google's official storage location, verifies it against a SHA512 checksum from Google's official CLI auto-updater manifest, and registers it on your PATH as `agy`. Both `x64` and `arm64` are supported.

Antigravity is proprietary software. By installing you accept Google's [terms](https://antigravity.google/terms).
    </description>
